MVVM (Model-View-ViewModel) is a popular architecture pattern for building iOS apps with Swift. However, Apple's SwiftUI framework is built on top of the Combine framework, which makes TCA (The Composable Architecture) a more natural fit. Clean Architecture, on the other hand, is a more abstract concept that emphasizes separating business logic from presentation logic. In Swift, you can use Combine to create a TCA-like architecture by using Publishers and Subscribers. For example:

let viewModel = @Published(
  ".currentValue", on: .main
)

let publisher = Timer.publish-every(1, on: .main, in: .common).
  .autoconnect()

publisher.sink { [weak self] _ in
  self?.viewModel.currentValue = Date()
}.store(in: &cancellables)

